Reminder: it is more important who you sign up with and listen to for colour analysis content rather than focussing on whether in person vs virtual is correct. Here are the things I recommend looking for when deciding a colour analysis professional to work with and listen to in content: 1) Accredited in person colour analysis training 2) Vast in person colour analysis experience 3) Client feedback after client has tried out colours for a bit (includes perhaps before and afters in their best hair, makeup, clothing colours) 4) Virtual colour analysis client feedback (if signing up for virtual service) 5) Ensuring you are happy with their colour analysis system used - eg in my opinion a 4 season system is not refined enough for everyone. Unfortunately with the rise in popularity of colour analysis, there has been a rise in people creating colour analysis content and charging you for colour analysis who have no business doing so ‚Äî BEWARE!
